ref: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.266, p.5087 (2008)
title: Study of proton induced reactions on niobium targets up to 70 MeV

x4freetext: Study of proton induced reactions on niobium targets
up to 70 MeV

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.266, p.5087 (2008)

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4freetext: High purity Nb foils (20 micron) as target material,
Al (0.5 and 1 mm) and Cu (54 micron) monitor foils.
High purity Ge gamma spectrometer
Stack containing Nb target and Al, Cu monitor foils
with other metal foils used as energy degrader and
target material in a parallel experiment was
irradiated in a Faraday cup like target holder for
half an hour at 200 nA with 70 MeV proton beam.
HPGe spectrometers at large source-detector distances
were used to assess the activity of the foils.
No chemical separation was used.
Measurement started 20 h after EOB and decay was
followed for about one month.
Excitation functions were determined
relative to the simultaneously re-measured
natAl(p,x)22,24Na and natCu(p,x)62,65Zn and 56Co
monitor reactions.
Energy degradation was calculated by using the
formulas and tables of Andersen and Ziegler.
Correction of 25% in beam intensity and 0.5 MeV in
incident particle energy were necessary to introduce
based on monitor reactions.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Nuclear Data Services (Doc. series of NDS), No.1211 (2001)

x4freetext: Chapter 4
The uncertainties of the mean proton energies
in the individual foils were estimated from the energy
uncertainties of the primary beam, thickness and
uniformity of the foils, energy straggling and energy
spread. The uncertainties on the energy of the
front foil of a stack are around 0.3 MeV and increase
up to 2.7 MeV for the last foils of the stack.
The estimated total uncertainty on the
cross-sections contains uncertainties of the following
linearly contributing sources:
* peak areas,
* efficiency,
* gamma abundances,
* number of target nuclei,
* beam intensity
total amount is about 12%.
Nonlinear contributions like time parameters are not
considered.
Measured cross sections were compared to the
values of model calculation ALICE.
Thick target production yields were calculated
from the fitted experimental cross sections.
Activity depth distribution was calculated for TLA use.
F. Ditroi, 2009.
